==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sectional
<hw>Sec"tion*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to a section or distinct part of larger body or territory;
local.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All <qex>sectional</qex> interests, or party feelings, it is
hoped, will hereafter yield to schemes of ambition.</q>
<rj><qau>Story.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consisting of sections, or capable of being divided
into sections; <as>as, a <ex>sectional</ex> steam boiler</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sectionalism</ent>⟦br⟧
